{"key":"processedPost-15530571","value":{"id":15530571,"first":15530558,"last":15530585,"when":1324151336,"utime":"12/17/11 09:48 PM","content":"The salt test has long been disproved for our use growing mushrooms.&nbsp; Hygrometers, when they're accurate at all, are only accurate through a very small portion of the scale.&nbsp; This is why cigar aficionados use the salt method, but mushroom growers use the damp towel method.<br /><br />Furthermore, if a hygrometer is off by 20% at one part of the scale, it's not going to be off by that same 20% at another part of the scale.&nbsp; You can't simply add or subtract the difference.<br />RR","title":"Re: Calibrate your hygrometer !","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}